Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 8
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the VAPB gene on chromosome 20.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 1
Definition: The most common type of familial ALS that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SOD1 gene on chromosome 21.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 2
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the alsin gene on chromosome 2.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 3
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in loci on chromosome 18.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 4
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SETX gene on chromosome 9.
Synonym: distal hereditary motor neuropathy with upper motor neuron signs

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 5
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SPG11 gene on chromosome 15q21.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 6
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FUS gene on chromosome 16.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 7
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in loci on chromosome 20.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 9
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ANG gene on chromosome 14.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 10
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TARDBP gene on chromosome 1.
Synonym: TARDBP-related frontotemporal lobar degeneration with TDP43 inclusions

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 11
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FIG4 gene on chromosome 6.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 12
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the OPTN gene on chromosome 10.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 13
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis where a mutation that has_material_basis_in the ATXN2 gene on chromosome 12 contributes to suscepitbility.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 14
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the VCP gene on chromosome 9.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 15
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the UBQLN2 gene on chromosome X.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 16
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SIGMAR1 gene (SETX) on chromosome 9.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 17
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHMP2B gene on chromosome 3.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 18
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the PFN1 gene on chromosome 17.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 19
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ERBB4 gene on chromosome 2.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 20
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with juvenile onset that has_material_basis_in mutation in the HNRNPA1 gene on chromosome 12.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 21
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the MATR3 gene on chromosome 5.

Name: FTDALS1
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the C9ORF72 gene on chromosome 9. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.

Name: FTDALS2
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHCHD10 gene on chromosome 22. It is characterized by adult onset of either frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.
Synonym: frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 2

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 22
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TUBA4A gene on chromosome 2q35.

Name: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 23
Definition: An epidermolysis bullosa dystrophica that is characterized by recurrent blistering at the level of the lamina densa secondary to minor trauma
Synonym: Primary mediastinal clear cell lymphoma of B-cell type

Name: juvenile amyotrophic lateral sclerosis with dementia
Definition: A juvenile amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that is slowly progressive with concomitantly progressive dementia.

Name: FTDALS3
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SQSTM1 gene on chromosome 5q35.
Synonym: frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 3

Name: FTDALS4
Definition: An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TBK1 gene on chromosome 12q14.
Synonym: frontotemporal dementia and/or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis 4
